    "recap_text": "LYNCHBURG, VA. \u2013\nThe Liberty Flames brought the go-ahead run to the plate in the home half of the ninth, only to come up short, falling to the No. 9 Virginia Cavaliers 14-12 on Wednesday at Worthington Field at Liberty Baseball Stadium.\nAfter falling behind 14-4 after six innings, the Flames whittled the Cavaliers' lead to 14-12 and put runners on the corners with two outs in their last at bat. However, reliever Lucas Hartman was able to retire the next batter to close out the victory.\nLiberty had a season-high 17 hits in the contest, highlighted by two home runs by first baseman\nRiley DeCandido\n. The first baseman drove in four runs.\nDesignated hitter\nJordan Jaffe\n, third baseman\nJaxon Sorenson\nand left fielder\nNick Barone\nhad three hits apiece for the Flames.\nLiberty falls to 13-7 on the season. Virginia moves to 18-4.\nBox Score Highlights\nRecords:\nVirginia (18-4); Liberty (13-7)\nLocation:\nWorthington Field at Liberty Baseball Stadium (Lynchburg, Va.)\nWP:\nMatt Augustin (1-0) \u00a0|\nLP:\nAyden Decker-Perry (1-3)\nScoring Summary\n1\nst\n\u2013 UVA \u2013 Didawick walked, Becker scored, 1-0\n1\nst\n\u2013 UVA \u2013 Murray walked, Tiroly scored, 2-0\n1\nst\n\u2013 UVA \u2013 Jackson hit by pitch, S. Harris scores, 3-0\n1\nst\n\u2013 UVA \u2013 Weatherspoon doubled, Jackson, Murray and Didawick score, 6-0\n1\nst\n\u2013 UVA \u2013 Becker singles, Weatherspoon scores, 7-0\n2\nnd\n\u2013 UVA \u2013 Murray flies out, S. Harris scores, 8-0\n2\nnd\n\u2013 UVA \u2013 Johnson flies out, Johnson scores, 9-0\n2\nnd\n\u2013 LIBERTY \u2013 Swofford reaches on a fielder's choice, Barone scores, 9-1\n4\nth\n\u2013 LIBERTY \u2013 DeCandido homers, 9-2\n4\nth\n\u2013 LIBERTY \u2013 Marsh triples, Campos and Swofford score, 9-4\n5\nth\n\u2013 UVA \u2013 Weatherspoon singles, Johnson scores, 10-4\n5\nth\n\u2013 UVA \u2013 Garcia singles, Becker and Weatherspoon, 12-4\n6\nth\n\u2013 UVA \u2013 Didawick homers, S. Harris scores, 14-4\n7\nth\n\u2013 LIBERTY \u2013 Swofford single, DeCandido scores, 14-5\n7\nth\n\u2013 LIBERTY \u2013 Anderson scores on a wild pitch, 14-7\n7\nth\n\u2013 LIBERTY \u2013 Drumm singles, Swofford scores, 14-8\n8\nth\n\u2013 LIBERTY \u2013 DeCandido homers, Sorenson scores, 14-10\n9\nth\n\u2013 LIBERTY \u2013 Sorenson singles, Drumm scores, 14-11\n9\nth\n\u2013 LIBERTY \u2013 Barone flies out, Jaffe scores, 14-12\nNotable Numbers\n- Liberty outhit Virginia, 17-9, in the contest. The Cavaliers committed two errors. The Flames made one error.\n- Liberty left 13 men on base. Virginia left four men on base.\n- DeCandido now leads the Flames with five home runs.\n- Flames shortstop\nTanner Marsh\nhad two hits, one an RBI triple, walked and drove in two runs.\n- Second baseman\nEaston Swofford\ncollected two hits, had two RBI and scored two runs for the Flames.\n- Liberty starter Ayden Decker-Petty takes the loss. The right-hander gave up five runs on one hit. He walked three batters.\n- Relievers\nCooper Harrington\nand\nTyler August\ncombined to not allow a run over the final three innings for the Flames.\n- Despite only pitching one inning, Virginia starter Matt Augustin was awarded the win. He did not allow a hit during the first inning. He struck out one and walked one.\n- Catcher Jake Weatherspoon had two hits, one a double, and four RBI for the Cavaliers.\n- Virginia left fielder Harrison Didawick collected two hits, including his second home run of the season, had three RBI and three runs scored.\nBeyond the Box Score\n- Today's contest was the first of two games between Liberty and Virginia this season. The Flames and Cavaliers will meet at Dishroon Stadium in Charlotteville on April 12.\n- Liberty's 17 hits are a season high. The Flames' previous high was 14 at UNCG in a 12-10 win last Tuesday.\n- DeCandido hits two home runs in a game for the second time this season. Last Tuesday, the first baseman belted two home runs in the Flames' 12-10 victory at UNCG.\n- Jaffe has at least one hit in each of his last six games. Designated hitter recorded his third three-hit and fifth multi-hit game of the season.\n-\nNick Barone\nposted his third three-hit and sixth multi-hit game of the season, while Sorenson collected his first three-hit game and third of the year.\n- With two hits in the game, Marsh now leads the Flames with seven multi-hit games.\n- Swofford had his first multi-hit game.\nUp Next\nLiberty takes to the road for a three-game Conference USA series at Kennesaw State. The series between the Flames and Owls at Mickey Dunn Stadium begins Friday. The first pitch is scheduled for 6 p.m."
